  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide marginalised community with immediate health care &amp; food and cash support</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Access to healthcare facilities are constrained in Jharkhand owing to its backwardness and difficult topography. The State also has a high number of migrants returning from the cities posing a risk of bringing back the infection with them. There are many vulnerable and poor households stuck in migrant destinations like Delhi NCR with little or no security around food and other basic materials The significant change the project is likely to bring are as follows: 
a) Communities, including returning migrants, will have easy access to identification, primary care and referral in case of COVID 19 symptoms and infection and there is a reduction in spread of COVID; b)  There is an increased uptake of COVID 19 vaccination c) Community systems including the response from local governance functionaries are more coordinated and in time d)  Cash transfer to families bring immediate sustenance and relief 500 HH and 250 HH in Delhi NCR</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The intervention is based in 3 districts of Jharkhand (Gumla, Simdega and Palamu) where the spread of Covid infection is more. Migrant issue is also enormous in this State. Intervention to focus on a) to establish 30 covid care centres in 30 villages of 3 districts covering 150 hamlets b) Around 10,000 symptomatic people likely to be identified through surveillance across 150 hamlets c) Approximately 3000 migrants returning to village to be kept in isolation centres and treated, if required d) Approximately 1000 serious cases to be referred to bigger hospitals for treatment e) Awareness on Covid appropriate behaviour and vaccination to be given to 15000 individuals f) 500 migrants to receive unconditional cash transfer of 5000/- in their bank account g) 500 HH to receive sanitary hygiene kits and apart from Jharkhand Phia to distribute dry ration and hygiene kits to 500 HH in Delhi/NCR region through volunteers.</narrative>
  </description>
